reviewText: I actually was interested in finding a DVD featuring the music of Alan Parsons, and I could never find anything. All of a sudden this DVD came out, and it is rock solid. A band in fine form, a great selection of songs (although I would have loved a version of Ammonia Avenue), just a great DVD. Nothing fancy about this one. No big stage show, or great graphics, just a solid performance. Some great tracks: Time, Prime Time, Dr. Tarr and Professor Fether, I wouldn't wanna be like you... and a very interesting fact: all of the band takes a lead vocal (with the exception of the keyboard player), and they do renditions of classic vocal performances by great vocalists.If you like Alan Parsons Project at all, this is a must have!

reviewText: I was always a fan of The Alan Parson Project and Alan Parsons, for decades now, but became an even bigger fan when I saw them live for the first time a few years ago at the California State Fair--their music and performance was mesmerizing on a warm summer night outdoors, right in the middle of the fairgrounds on the main stage there.  While nothing beats seeing them live, this DVD is a nice reminder (and individual experience) that comes close to approximating that live experience.  Highly recommended.
summary: Alan Parsons Project at their best

reviewText: Very simple stage show, not a big production, so don't expect much in the way of trick lighting or effects. Musicianship and song line-up are excellent. Sound quality is good, but surprised it's only in stereo. This DVD would be much better if mixed in 5.1 or DTS surround. Would have given 5 stars if in surround sound.

reviewText: Eric Woolfson. He is half of the Alan Parsons Project- probably even greater than half.  His voice is the lead on songs like Eye in the Sky, Time and Don't Answer Me.  He recently passed away but in 2004 he was still very much alive.  Alan Parson's voice is nowhere near as great and neither is this punk singing lead, prancing around the stage with his black fingernail polish.  The band and the backing vocals are tight, but not having Eric Woolfson in this is a huge disappointment.
Title: N/A

reviewText: Even though the video quality is not up to today's standards (it's 1.33 with 2 channel stereo)it beats the heck out of nothing! It's Alan Parsons live, man!! Something I thought I would NEVER see on video! Maybe because I'm a fan...I'm easier on the review. But, man...IT'S ALAN PARSONS LIVE!!! Good concert, waaay to short (at 80 minutes) but better than nothin' at all. Enjoy it for what it's worth. Hey, it's not Blu-Ray...it will definately do!!! If you're a fan, get this German all region import DVD before it's out of print.
summary: Hey, we'll take it! It's Alan Parsons live on DVD!!!

reviewText: This is a great DVD with great sound, camera work and song selection.The only disappointment I had (which cost this DVD a star) was the sound levels (or lack of)it was either recorded at or mixed at.When this DVD is at max volume, it's not very loud.If you live in an apartment with neighbors all around, that might not be an issue but I live in the country and like to crank my performances.Great DVD.

reviewText: Alan Parsons music has always leaned more towards relaxation than stimulation.  No surround sound, somewhat weak stereo, and very little stage presence but if you like Alan Parsons music there's nothing to dislike and every song is played well by very competent musicians, even though there's not much dynamic stage presence or WOW factor.
